Package grammarModel.structure

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ISyntacticBranch
    ISyntacticBranch is a syntactic structure that represents the derivation of a non-terminal node in a syntactic tree.
    ISyntacticGrove
    ISyntacticGrove is a container of syntactic trees, i.e. syntactic branches whose name is the start element of the context-free grammar at use.
    ISyntacticLeaf
    ISyntacticLeaf is a terminal syntactic structure, that has no component and is only characterized by its name and ID.
    ISyntacticStructure
    ISyntacticStructure is an abstract class that is used to represent the nodes of a syntactic tree.
